    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/4–1552</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum on the Events of April 14, by the Deputy Assistant
                        Secretary of State for Far Eastern Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                            >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-04-15">April 15,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Korean Armistice Negotiations</item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RGMB1">General Ridgway</persName>’s C 66832<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d87fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d87">Supra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note> was discussed the morning of April 14 with the Secretary, the
                    Under Secretary, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName>, Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName>, Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_AJM1">Allison</persName> and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                        >Johnson</persName>. As a result of that meeting, a meeting with the <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> was requested and held early in the afternoon
                    of April 14,<note n="2" xml:id="d87fn2">For the substance of discussion of this
                        meeting, see the memorandum, <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d88">infra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note> at which <persName corresp="#p_BGOTAON1">General
                        Bradley</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CGJL1">General Collins</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_VGHS1">General Vandenberg</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_FAWN1">Admiral Fechteler</persName> were present for the <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BCE1"
                        >Bohlen</persName>, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName>, Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_AJM1">Allison</persName> and Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> for State. There was a general
                    discussion of problems raised by the fact that the screening thus far indicated
                    a far higher portion of prisoners of war who would violently object to
                    repatriation than had been anticipated. A radio to <persName corresp="#p_RGMB1"
                        >General Ridgway</persName> on the subject was discussed after the meeting
                    and drafted by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_BELGCL1">General Bolte</persName>. The radio, together with some
                    subsequent minor changes suggested by State, was approved by the <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> and subsequently by the President with whom it
                    was discussed by <persName corresp="#p_BGOTAON1">General Bradley</persName> and
                        <pb facs="0179" n="145" xml:id="pg_145"/> the Secretary of State. It was
                    despatched the same afternoon as <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>
                        906314.<note n="3" xml:id="d87fn3">Dated Apr. 15, <ref target="#pg_152">p.
                            152</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
